Interface NativeArray

All Superinterfaces:
CanBeNativeCapable, NativeCapable, NativeFieldContainer, NativeObjectFieldContainer, NativeSingleFieldContainer
All Known Subinterfaces:
CanBeNativeCapableArray, NativeArrayOfArray, NativeBehaviorReflectionArray, NativeBooleanArray, NativeBooleanObjectArray, NativeByteArray, NativeByteObjectArray, NativeCapableArray, NativeCharacterArray, NativeCharacterObjectArray, NativeConstructorReflectionArray, NativeDoubleArray, NativeDoubleObjectArray, NativeFieldMethodReflectionArray, NativeFloatArray, NativeFloatObjectArray, NativeIntegerArray, NativeIntegerObjectArray, NativeLongArray, NativeLongObjectArray, NativeMemberReflectionArray, NativeMethodReflectionArray, NativeNumberArray, NativeNumberObjectArray, NativeObjectArray, NativePrimitiveArray, NativePrimitiveObjectArray, NativeShortArray, NativeShortObjectArray, NativeStringAnsiArray, NativeStringArray, NativeStringBufferAnsiArray, NativeStringBufferArray, NativeStringBufferUnicodeArray, NativeStringUnicodeArray
public interface NativeArray
extends CanBeNativeCapable

The NativeArray is the interface implemented by native capable classes working as wrappers of arrays (String[], MyStructure[], int[], int[][] etc).

The contained elements may be objects ("can be native" and native capable) or primitive values (int, long etc).

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria

Method Detail

getElement

java.lang.Object getElement(int index,
                            int fetchMode)
Returns the element at the specified index. If instance is native the returned object is synchronized with the native memory fetching data with the specified deepness.

If is not native it works as a normal array.

If a primitive array the element is wrapped.

Parameters:
index - the zero-based index of the element.
fetchMode - the fetch method to copy from native memory.
Returns:
the object element at the specified index.
See Also:
NativeManager.fetch(Object,int)

setElement

void setElement(int index,
                java.lang.Object value,
                int unFetchMode)
Sets the element at the specified index with the new value. If instance is native the native memory is updated unfetching data with the specified deepness.

If is not native it works as a normal array.

If a primitive array the element must be a wrapper.

Parameters:
index - the zero-based index of the element.
value - the new value at the specified position.
unFetchMode - the "unfetch" method to copy from native memory.
See Also:
NativeManager.unFetch(Object,int)
